1 HOUSE BILL NO. 142
2 INTRODUCED BY L. SCHUBERT, S. FITZPATRICK
3
4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO INTERIM COMMITTEE BILL
5 DRAFTS; CLARIFYING THE TERM "PARTISAN BASIS"; INCREASING THE NUMBER OF DRAFT
6 REQUESTS THAT CAN BE REQUESTED ON A PARTISAN BASIS; AMENDING SECTION 5-5-215, MCA;
7 AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 5-5-215, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "5-5-215. Duties of interim committees. (1) Each interim committee shall:
13 (a) review administrative rules within its jurisdiction;
14 (b) subject to 5-5-217(3), conduct interim studies as assigned;
15 (c) monitor the operation of assigned executive branch agencies with specific attention to the
16 following:
17 (i) identification of issues likely to require future legislative attention;
18 (ii) opportunities to improve existing law through the analysis of problems experienced with the
19 application of the law by an agency; and
20 (iii) experiences of the state's citizens with the operation of an agency that may be amenable to
21 improvement through legislative action;
22 (d) review, if requested by any member of the interim committee, the statutorily established
23 advisory councils and required reports of assigned agencies to make recommendations to the next legislature
24 on retention or elimination of any advisory council or required reports pursuant to 5-11-210;
25 (e) review proposed legislation of assigned agencies or entities as provided in the joint legislative
26 rules;
27 (f) accumulate, compile, analyze, and furnish information bearing upon its assignment and
28 relevant to existing or prospective legislation as it determines, on its own initiative, to be pertinent to the
