1 adequate completion of its work; and
2 (g) review proposed statewide initiatives as defined in 13-27-110 within the interim committee's
3 subject area and vote to either support or not support the placement of the text of the proposed statewide
4 initiative on the ballot in accordance with 13-27-228.
5 (2) Each interim committee shall prepare bills and resolutions that, in its opinion, the welfare of the
6 state may require for presentation to the next regular session of the legislature. An interim committee may by
7 vote request four five bill drafts on a partisan basis and an unlimited number of bill drafts on a bipartisan basis.
8 (3) The legislative services division shall keep accurate records of the activities and proceedings of
9 each interim committee.
10 (4) As used in this section:
11 (a) "bipartisan basis" means a vote in which members from more than one party vote to request a
12 bill draft; and
13 (b) "partisan basis" means a vote in which members from only one the majority party vote to
14 request a bill draft."
15
16 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Effective date. [This act] is effective on passage and approval.
17 - END -
